// ================== FIRMWARE v1.1.1 — SOFT START MERGED ==================
// Base: v1.1.1 debugged (all FIX-01…FIX-11 intact, zero lines disturbed)
// Merge: RS775 soft-start via BC847B transistor on PWM_PIN 25
//
// NEW HARDWARE PIN:
//   PWM_PIN 25  — BC847B base through 1 kΩ resistor (soft-start switch)
//
// EXISTING PINS — UNCHANGED:
//   RELAY_PWR  5   → K3 main bypass relay  (was direct power; now bypass)
//   RELAY_FWD 18   → K1 forward direction relay
//   RELAY_REV 19   → K2 reverse direction relay
//   LIMIT_SWITCH_PIN 27, BUZZER_PIN 23, SDA 21, SCL 22  — all untouched
//
// SOFT-START SEQUENCE (startMotor):
//   1. clearRelays() — all off + PWM 0                (shoot-through safe)
//   2. Direction relay (FWD or REV) ON                (K1 or K2)
//   3. RELAY_PWR (bypass K3) stays OFF
//   4. softStart() — ramp PWM 0→255 over ~2.5 s       (transistor limits I)
//   5. Bypass relay (K3) ON — transistor bypassed      (full power)
//   6. PWM held at 255 (transistor still saturated, relay carries load)
//
// SOFT-STOP SEQUENCE (stopMotor):
//   1. RELAY_PWR (bypass K3) OFF first                (current to transistor)
//   2. Ramp PWM 255→0 over ~2.5 s                    (smooth current decay)
//   3. PWM = 0, direction relays OFF                  (fully off)
//
// ALL FIX-01…FIX-11 comments preserved verbatim.
// BUZZER: zero changes.
// =========================================================================




